<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-12-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="680" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d680">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 777.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-12-05"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 5, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your very interesting despatch of the 19th
                            of November (No. 537) has been received, together with the pamphlet on
                            the foreign enlistment act of Great Britain by Mr. Gibbs, which is
                            highly appreciated.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c, &amp;c, &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>